From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: local-loongarch64-adaptation <local@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 11:10:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] platforms 0.0.8: add loongarch64 CPU constraint

Reason:
rules_rust 0.42.1 originally depends on bazelbuild/platforms 0.0.8.
That release has no @platforms//cpu:loongarch64 constraint, so any
rules_rust mapping from the Rust triple loongarch64-unknown-linux-gnu to
Bazel constraints cannot resolve.

This is a minimal backport of bazelbuild/platforms commit
dbae6fcce51b11029fe8d41c34747dffc0b85715. It is only needed if you must
stay on platforms 0.0.8 instead of upgrading to platforms 1.1.0.

diff --git a/cpu/BUILD b/cpu/BUILD
index 6497452..e7afb92 100644
--- a/cpu/BUILD
+++ b/cpu/BUILD
@@ -188,3 +188,8 @@ constraint_value(
     name = "riscv64",
     constraint_setting = ":cpu",
 )
+
+constraint_value(
+    name = "loongarch64",
+    constraint_setting = ":cpu",
+)
